TITLE: Creating a Basic Layout Component in Gatsby (JSX)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a simple layout component in Gatsby using JSX. It imports React and defines a functional component named `Layout` that accepts `children` as a prop and wraps them in a `div` with specified styling. This layout component is intended to provide a consistent structure across multiple pages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/how-to/routing/layout-components.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import React from "react"

export default function Layout({ children }) {
  return (
    <div style={{ margin: `0 auto`, maxWidth: 650, padding: `0 1rem` }}>
      {children}
    </div>
  )
}
```

