TITLE: Creating PrivateRoute Component (React/JSX)
DESCRIPTION: This React component, PrivateRoute, is a higher-order component that protects routes from unauthorized access. It checks if the user is logged in using the `isLoggedIn` function. If the user is not logged in and is not trying to access the login page, it redirects them to the '/app/login' route. Otherwise, it renders the wrapped component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/tutorial/authentication-tutorial.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import React from "react"
import { navigate } from "gatsby"
import { isLoggedIn } from "../services/auth"

const PrivateRoute = ({ component: Component, location, ...rest }) => {
  if (!isLoggedIn() && location.pathname !== `/app/login`) {
    navigate("/app/login")
    return null
  }

  return <Component {...rest} />
}

export default PrivateRoute
```

