TITLE: StaticQuery Typechecking with PropTypes in Gatsby with JSX
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to implement typechecking with PropTypes while using StaticQuery in Gatsby. It imports React, StaticQuery, graphql, and PropTypes. A separate Header component is created to handle the rendering, and a MyHeader component wraps it with StaticQuery to fetch data and pass it to the Header component. PropTypes are used to define the expected shape of the data prop in the Header component, ensuring type safety.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/how-to/querying-data/static-query.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JSX
CODE:
```
import React from "react"
import { StaticQuery, graphql } from "gatsby"
import PropTypes from "prop-types"

const Header = ({ data }) => (
  <header>
    <h1>{data.site.siteMetadata.title}</h1>
  </header>
)

export default function MyHeader(props) {
  return (
    <StaticQuery
      query={graphql`
        query {
          site {
            siteMetadata {
              title
            }
          }
        }
      `}
      render={data => <Header data={data} {...props} />} 
    />
  )
}

Header.propTypes = {
  data: PropTypes.shape({
    site: PropTypes.shape({
      siteMetadata: PropTypes.shape({
        title: PropTypes.string.isRequired,
      }).isRequired,
    }).isRequired,
  }).isRequired,
}
```

