TITLE: Filter with GraphQL - Regex Operator
DESCRIPTION: This query filters MarkdownRemark nodes to find titles that do not start with 'T' using the `regex` operator. The regular expression `/^[^T]/` is used.  It shows how to use regular expressions for pattern matching in GraphQL filters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/graphql-reference.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
{
  # regex: I want all the titles that do not start with 'T' -- this is what /^[^T]/ means.
  # To learn more about regular expressions: https://regexr.com/
  example_regex: allMarkdownRemark(
    filter: { frontmatter: { title: { regex: "/^[^T]/" } } }
  ) {
    edges {
      node {
        frontmatter {
          title
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

