TITLE: Create Schema Customization with Default Field Value
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to set a default value for a field using a custom resolver. It defines a `Frontmatter` type with a `tags` field and a resolver that returns `['uncategorized']` if the `tags` field is null or an empty array.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/reference/graphql-data-layer/schema-customization.md#_snippet_27

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
exports.createSchemaCustomization = ({ actions, schema }) => {
  const { createTypes } = actions
  const typeDefs = [
    "type MarkdownRemark implements Node { frontmatter: Frontmatter }",
    schema.buildObjectType({
      name: "Frontmatter",
      fields: {
        tags: {
          type: "[String!]",
          resolve(source, args, context, info) {
            // For a more generic solution, you could pick the field value from
            // `source[info.fieldName]`
            const { tags } = source
            if (source.tags == null || (Array.isArray(tags) && !tags.length)) {
              return ["uncategorized"]
            }
            return tags
          },
        },
      },
    }),
  ]
  createTypes(typeDefs)
}
```

