TITLE: Tap into Resolve Hook for Original Request Path
DESCRIPTION: This snippet taps into the `resolve` hook to store the original request path in `_gatsbyThemeShadowingOriginalRequestPath`. This allows access to the original file name later in the `before-resolved` hook. It's used to enable shadowing of files with different extensions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/conceptual/how-shadowing-works.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
apply(resolver) {
    // This hook is executed very early and captures the original file name
    resolver
      .getHook(`resolve`)
      .tapAsync(
        `GatsbyThemeComponentShadowingResolverPlugin`,
        (request, stack, callback) => {
          if (!request._gatsbyThemeShadowingOriginalRequestPath) {
            request._gatsbyThemeShadowingOriginalRequestPath = request.request
          }
          return callback()
        }
      )
```

