TITLE: Handling process is not defined error in Gatsby
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to handle the `process is not defined` error in Gatsby v3.  Webpack 4 automatically polyfilled `process`, but webpack 5 does not.  This example shows how to use `typeof window !== "undefined"` instead of `process.browser`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/reference/release-notes/migrating-from-v2-to-v3.md#_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
import React from "react"

const Base64 = ({ text }) => {
  let base64;
-  if (process.browser) {
+  if (typeof window !== "undefined") {
    base64 = btoa(text)
  } else {
    base64 = Buffer.from(text).toString('base64')
  }

  return (
    <div>
      {base64}
    </div>
  )
}

export default Base64
```

