TITLE: Filter with GraphQL - Not In Operator
DESCRIPTION: This query filters MarkdownRemark nodes to find titles that are neither "Children's Anthology of Monsters" nor "Hogwarts: A History" using the `nin` operator. It excludes values that are present in the specified array.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/graphql-reference.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
{
  # nin: I want all the titles and dates from `frontmatter`
  # where the title is neither
  # - "Children's Anthology of Monsters", nor
  # - "Hogwarts: A History".
  example_nin: allMarkdownRemark(
    filter: {
      frontmatter: {
        title: {
          nin: ["Children's Anthology of Monsters", "Hogwarts: A History"]
        }
      }
    }
  ) {
    edges {
      node {
        frontmatter {
          title
          date
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

