TITLE: Typing the data prop in a Gatsby page using PageProps
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to use generics with `PageProps` to type the `data` prop in a Gatsby page component. It defines a `DataProps` type and uses it as a generic for `PageProps` to provide type information for the `site` property.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/how-to/custom-configuration/typescript.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import * as React from "react"
import { graphql, PageProps } from "gatsby"

type DataProps = {
  site: {
    siteMetadata: {
      title: string
    }
  }
}

const IndexRoute = ({ data: { site } }: PageProps<DataProps>) => {
  return (
    <main>
      <h1>{site.siteMetadata.title}</h1>
    </main>
  )
}

export default IndexRoute

export const query = graphql`
  {
    site {
      siteMetadata {
        title
      }
    }
  }
`
```

