TITLE: Updating Page Templates in Gatsby MDX
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the changes required in page templates when migrating to Gatsby Plugin MDX v4. It includes removing the import of `MDXRenderer` and using the `children` prop directly to render the MDX content, as well as removing the `body` field from the GraphQL query.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/packages/gatsby-plugin-mdx/README.md#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
import React from "react"
import { graphql } from "gatsby"
- import { MDXRenderer } from "gatsby-plugin-mdx"

- function PostTemplate({ data: { mdx } }) {
+ function PostTemplate({ data: { mdx }, children }) {

  return (
    <main>
      <h1>{mdx.frontmatter.title}</h1>
-     <MDXRenderer>
-       {mdx.body}
-     </MDXRenderer>
+     {children}
    </main>
  )
}

 export const pageQuery = graphql`
  query PostTemplate($id: String!) {
    mdx(id: { eq: $id }) {
      frontmatter {
        title
      }
-     body
    }
  }
`

export default PostTemplate
```

