TITLE: Focusing Skip Link on Route Update (Gatsby Browser API)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet uses the onRouteUpdate browser API in gatsby-browser.js to automatically focus the skip link when navigating to a new page. It selects the element with the data-reach-skip-link attribute (added by the SkipNavLink component) and calls the focus() method. This improves accessibility by placing focus on an interactive element after navigation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/examples/using-reach-skip-nav/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// gatsby-browser.js

export const onRouteUpdate = ({ location, prevLocation }) => {
  if (prevLocation !== null) {
    const skipLink = document.querySelector("[data-reach-skip-link]") //this is the query selector that comes with the <SkipNavLink> component
    if (skipLink) {
      skipLink.focus()
    }
  }
}
```

