TITLE: Webpack configuration for replacing a module
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to customize the webpack configuration in `gatsby-node.js` to replace a problematic module with a null loader during the HTML build process. It targets the `build-html` and `develop-html` stages and uses the `loaders.null()` function to effectively remove the module from the build.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/debugging-html-builds.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
exports.onCreateWebpackConfig = ({ stage, loaders, actions }) => {
  if (stage === "build-html" || stage === "develop-html") {
    actions.setWebpackConfig({
      module: {
        rules: [
          {
            test: /bad-module/,
            use: loaders.null(),
          },
        ],
      },
    })
  }
}
```

