TITLE: Query with Variables in GraphQL
DESCRIPTION: This GraphQL query defines a query named `GetBlogPosts` that accepts three variables: `$limit`, `$filter`, and `$sort`. These variables are then used as arguments to the `allMarkdownRemark` query, allowing for dynamic control over the query's behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/graphql-reference.md#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
query GetBlogPosts(
  $limit: Int
  $filter: MarkdownRemarkFilterInput
  $sort: MarkdownRemarkSortInput
) {
  allMarkdownRemark(limit: $limit, filter: $filter, sort: $sort) {
    edges {
      node {
        frontmatter {
          title
          date(formatString: "dddd DD MMMM YYYY")
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

