TITLE: Initializing and Using WorkerPool in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code demonstrates how to initialize and use the `WorkerPool` class to execute tasks in worker processes. It creates a `WorkerPool` instance, specifies the path to the worker module, the number of workers, environment variables, and whether output should be silenced. It then queues tasks using `workerPool.all` and `workerPool.single`.
