TITLE: Create AuthorBio Component with GraphQL Fragment (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code defines a React component called `AuthorBio` that renders author information.  It uses a GraphQL fragment called `AuthorBio` to declare the data it needs from the `WpUser` type, including `id`, `name`, and `description`. It imports React and graphql from gatsby.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/packages/gatsby-source-wordpress/docs/tutorials/querying-data.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import React from "react"
import { graphql } from "gatsby"

export const AuthorFragment = graphql`
  fragment AuthorBio on WpUser {
    id
    name
    description
  }
`

const AuthorBio = ({ author: { id, name, description } }) => {
  return (
    <div className={`author-${id}`}>
      <h2>{name}</h2>
      <div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: description }} />
    </div>
  )
}

export default AuthorBio
```

