TITLE: Parsing TSV Files with extensions and delimiter Options (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example configures the gatsby-transformer-csv plugin to parse TSV (Tab-Separated Values) files instead of the default CSV files. It uses the `extensions` option to specify that files with the `.tsv` extension should be parsed and the `delimiter` option to set the delimiter character to a tab (`\t`).  This customization allows the plugin to handle different file formats beyond standard CSV.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/packages/gatsby-transformer-csv/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// In your gatsby-config.js
module.exports = {
  plugins: [
    {
      resolve: `gatsby-source-filesystem`,
      options: {
        name: `data`,
        path: `${__dirname}/src/data/`,
      },
    },
    {
      resolve: `gatsby-transformer-csv`,
      options: {
        extensions: [`tsv`],
        delimiter: '\t'
      },
    },
  ];
}
```

