TITLE: Adding Custom Query Field with Arguments in gatsby-node.js
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to add a custom root query field called `contributors` that accepts an argument `receivedSwag` to filter contributors based on whether they have received swag or not.  The `args` configuration defines the expected GraphQL argument. It uses `context.nodeModel.findAll` with a filter that uses the argument value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/reference/graphql-data-layer/schema-customization.md#_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
exports.createResolvers = ({ createResolvers }) => {
  const resolvers = {
    Query: {
      contributors: {
        type: ["ContributorJson"],
        args: {
          receivedSwag: "Boolean!",
        },
        resolve: async (source, args, context, info) => {
          const { entries } = await context.nodeModel.findAll({
            query: {
              filter: {
                receivedSwag: { eq: args.receivedSwag },
              },
            },
            type: "ContributorJson",
          })

          return entries
        },
      },
    },
  }
  createResolvers(resolvers)
}
```

