TITLE: Flex Page Component with Conditional Rendering
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet showcases a FlexPage component that conditionally renders different components based on the `type` property of elements within a `components` array. This is a common pattern in headless CMS setups where content editors can define page layouts.  The components Header, Text and Carousel need to be defined.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/examples/using-loadable-components/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
// src/components/flex-page.jsx
import * as React from "react"

const FlexPage = ({ components }) => {
  return (
    <>
      {components.map(component => {
        switch (component.type) {
          case "header":
            return <Header {...component} />
          case "text":
            return <Text {...component} />
          case "carousel":
            return <Carousel {...component} />
          default:
            return <div>empty</div>
        }
      })}
    </>
  )
}

export default FlexPage
```

