TITLE: Creating a Link Resolver Function
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code defines a link resolver function that generates URLs based on the document type and unique identifier (UID) from Prismic. It returns a specific URL structure for 'post' document types (e.g., '/blog/{unique slug}') and a default root URL for other document types. This function is used to create dynamic links to Prismic content within the Gatsby site.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/tutorial/prismic-source-graphql-tutorial.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
exports.linkResolver = function linkResolver(doc) {
  // Route for blog posts
  if (doc.type === "post") {
    return "/blog/" + doc.uid
  }
  // Homepage route fallback
  return "/"
}
```

