TITLE: Implementing onCreatePage API (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet implements the Gatsby `onCreatePage` API to modify pages dynamically. It checks if a page's path starts with '/app/' and, if so, sets the `matchPath` property to '/app/*', effectively making it a client-only route. This configuration allows @reach/router to handle the routing for these pages on the client-side.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/tutorial/authentication-tutorial.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Implement the Gatsby API “onCreatePage”. This is
// called after every page is created.
exports.onCreatePage = async ({ page, actions }) => {
  const { createPage } = actions

  // page.matchPath is a special key that's used for matching pages
  // only on the client.
  if (page.path.match(/^\/app/)) {
    page.matchPath = "/app/*"

    // Update the page.
    createPage(page)
  }
}
```

