TITLE: Displaying API Data in Gatsby SSR Page JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to access and display data fetched by the `getServerData` function within a Gatsby page component. The `serverData` prop is used to render a dynamic dog image based on the URL returned by the API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/how-to/rendering-options/using-server-side-rendering.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import * as React from "react"

const SSRPage = ({ serverData }) => ( // highlight-line
  <main>
    <h1>SSR Page with Dogs</h1>
    {/* highlight-next-line */}
    <img alt="Happy dog" src={serverData.message} />
  </main>
)

export default SSRPage

export async function getServerData() {
  try {
    const res = await fetch(`https://dog.ceo/api/breeds/image/random`)

    if (!res.ok) {
      throw new Error(`Response failed`)
    }

    return {
      props: await res.json(),
    }
  } catch (error) {
    return {
      status: 500,
      headers: {},
      props: {}
    }
  }
}
```

