TITLE: Initializing Post and Author Types with Basic Fields in Gatsby
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the initial definition of `Post` and `Author` types in Gatsby using `createSchemaCustomization`. It creates two GraphQL types, `Post` and `Author`, both implementing the `Node` interface and defining an `id` field of type `ID!`. This is a foundational step for defining data structures in Gatsby's GraphQL schema.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/tutorial/creating-a-source-plugin/part-3/index.mdx#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import type { GatsbyNode } from "gatsby"

export const createSchemaCustomization: GatsbyNode[`createSchemaCustomization`] =
  ({ actions }) => {
    const { createTypes } = actions

    createTypes(`
      type Post implements Node {
        id: ID!
      }

      type Author implements Node {
        id: ID!
      }
    `)
  }
```

