TITLE: Setting up SVG for Choropleth with d3v4
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code snippet sets up the SVG element for a Choropleth map using d3v4. It appends an SVG element to the specified selection and sets its width and height based on the provided measurements, maintaining a 1.6 aspect ratio. The function expects a d3 selection and a measurements object containing the width.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/examples/using-javascript-transforms/src/articles/2017-03-09-choropleth-on-d3v4/_choropleth.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
graph.setup = (selection, measurements) => {
  // the path string is drawn expecting:
  // a width of 950px
  // a height of 600px
  // which gives an aspect ratio of 1.6

  let svg = selection
    .append("svg")
    .attr("width", measurements.width)
    .attr("height", measurements.width / 1.6)

  return svg
}
```

