TITLE: Checking if window is defined in React
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to check if the `window` object is defined within a React component, which is crucial when dealing with browser-specific code that shouldn't run during server-side rendering. It uses a simple boolean flag to determine whether the code is running in a browser environment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/debugging-html-builds.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JSX
CODE:
```
import * as React from "react"

// Check if window is defined (so if in the browser or in node.js).
const isBrowser = typeof window !== "undefined"

export default function MyComponent() {
  let loggedIn = false
  if (isBrowser) {
    window.localStorage.getItem("isLoggedIn") === "true"
  }

  return <div>Am I logged in? {loggedIn}</div>
}
```

