TITLE: Handling require with expression in Gatsby
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to handle `require with expression` or `require.context` when importing file assets in Gatsby v3. The `.default` property must be appended to the require statement to make it work with ES Modules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/reference/release-notes/migrating-from-v2-to-v3.md#_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
import React from "react"
import { Helmet } from "react-helmet";

const Layout = ({ children, font }) => (
  <div>
    <Helmet>
-      <link rel="preload" href={require('../assets/fonts/' + font + '.woff2')} as="fonts/woff2" crossOrigin="anonymous" type="font/woff2" />
+      <link rel="preload" href={require('../assets/fonts/' + font + '.woff2').default} as="fonts/woff2" crossOrigin="anonymous" type="font/woff2" /
    </Helmet>
    {children}
  </div>
)

export default Layout
```

