TITLE: Using createMutex in Gatsby Core Utils
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the `createMutex` API from `gatsby-core-utils` to safely perform concurrent processes. It acquires a mutex, writes to a file, and then releases the mutex, ensuring that only one worker can access the file at a time.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/reference/release-notes/v4.8/index.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
