TITLE: Using the BlogPosts Component
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to integrate the `BlogPosts` component into the `Home` component to display a list of blog posts on the home page. The posts data is passed as a prop to the `BlogPosts` component, which renders the list of blog posts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/tutorial/prismic-source-graphql-tutorial.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: JSX
CODE:
```
export default function Home({ data }) {
  const doc = data.prismic.allBlog_homes.edges.slice(0, 1).pop()
  const posts = data.prismic.allPosts.edges

  if (!doc) return null

  return (
    <Layout>
      <div>
        <img src={doc.node.image.url} alt={doc.node.image.alt} />
        <h1>{RichText.asText(doc.node.headline)}</h1>
        <p>{RichText.asText(doc.node.description)}</p>
      </div>
      <BlogPosts posts={posts} /> //highlight-line
    </Layout>
  )
}
```

