TITLE: Opting out of Type Inference
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code snippet demonstrates how to use the `@dontInfer` directive to opt out of Gatsby's automatic type inference.  This requires explicitly defining all fields for the `AuthorJson` type, but can improve performance for larger projects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/reference/graphql-data-layer/schema-customization.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
exports.createSchemaCustomization = ({ actions }) => {
  const { createTypes } = actions
  const typeDefs = `
    type AuthorJson implements Node @dontInfer {
      name: String!
      firstName: String!
      email: String!
      joinedAt: Date
    }
  `
  createTypes(typeDefs)
}
```

