TITLE: Sort Results with GraphQL
DESCRIPTION: This query sorts results in ascending order based on the `date` field within `frontmatter`. It uses the `sort` argument to specify the field and the order (ASC).  The query retrieves the title and date for each node.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/graphql-reference.md#_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
{
  allMarkdownRemark(sort: { frontmatter: { date: ASC } }) {
    totalCount
    edges {
      node {
        frontmatter {
          title
          date
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

