TITLE: Use onPluginInit for reporter.setErrorMap
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the `onPluginInit` API for the `reporter.setErrorMap` function.  The function must be run inside `onPluginInit` instead of `onPreInit` for Gatsby v4 compatibility.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/docs/reference/release-notes/migrating-from-v3-to-v4.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const ERROR_MAP = {
  10000: {
    text: context => context.sourceMessage,
    level: "ERROR",
    category: "SYSTEM",
  },
}

exports.onPluginInit = ({ reporter }) => {
  reporter.setErrorMap(ERROR_MAP)
}
```

