TITLE: Plugin Configuration in gatsby-config.js - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to configure the `gatsby-plugin-schema-snapshot` plugin within the `gatsby-config.js` file.  It sets the path for the schema file, excludes a specific plugin (`gatsby-source-npm-package-search`), and conditionally updates the schema based on an environment variable. It requires the `process` object to access environment variables.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/packages/gatsby-plugin-schema-snapshot/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// gatsby-config.js
module.exports = {
  plugins: [
    {
      resolve: `gatsby-plugin-schema-snapshot`,
      options: {
        path: `schema.gql`,
        exclude: {
          plugins: [`gatsby-source-npm-package-search`],
        },
        update: process.env.GATSBY_UPDATE_SCHEMA_SNAPSHOT,
      },
    },
  ],
}
```

