TITLE: Node Interface Definition in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This Typescript interface defines the structure of a Gatsby node.  It includes properties for id, children, parent, fields, and an internal object containing metadata such as contentDigest, mediaType, type, owner, fieldOwners, content, and description.  The interface also allows for additional, node-specific fields via a string index signature.
