TITLE: CSS Blink Animation Removal
DESCRIPTION: This CSS snippet from `src/style/Product.scss` defines the `blink` animation. This code can be removed if the animation is no longer used. It uses keyframes to alternate the opacity of the element.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/docs/tutorial/e-commerce-with-datocms-and-snipcart/index.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: CSS
CODE:
```
@keyframes blink {
  $steps: 20;

  @for $i from 0 through $steps {
    #{percentage($i * (1 / $steps) + ((15 - random(30)) / 15) * (1 / $steps))} {
      @if ($i % 3 == 0) {
        opacity: 1;
      } @else {
        opacity: 0;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

