TITLE: Removing theme-color meta tag in gatsby-plugin-manifest using JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to prevent gatsby-plugin-manifest from adding the `theme-color` meta tag to the HTML output.  Setting `theme_color_in_head` to `false` in the plugin options disables this behavior, allowing for programmatic control of the tag.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/packages/gatsby-plugin-manifest/README.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// in gatsby-config.js
module.exports = {
  plugins: [
    {
      resolve: `gatsby-plugin-manifest`,
      options: {
        name: `GatsbyJS`,
        short_name: `GatsbyJS`,
        start_url: `/`,
        background_color: `#f7f0eb`,
        theme_color: `#a2466c`,
        display: `standalone`,
        icon: `src/images/icon.png`,
        theme_color_in_head: false, // This will avoid adding theme-color meta tag.
      },
    },
  ],
}
```

