TITLE: GraphQL Query Filtering by Category in Gatsby
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates a GraphQL query in Gatsby's `createPages` function. The query retrieves WordPress posts, filtering them based on a specific category. This can lead to issues because category updates aren't previewable, meaning previewing a post with a newly assigned category won't reflect the changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/packages/gatsby-source-wordpress/docs/features/preview.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
exports.createPages = async ({ graphql }) => {
  const graphqlResult = await graphql(/* GraphQL */ `
    query {
      allWpPost(
        filter: {
          categories: { nodes: { elemMatch: { name: { eq: "Blog" } } } }
        }
      ) {
        edges {
          node {
            id
            uri
          }
        }
      }
    }
  `)
}
```

