TITLE: RCE Prevention Test: Write Malicious File JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet attempts to write a file containing JavaScript code that should not be executed. It utilizes the `fs` module to write to a file named `file-to-attempt-rce-on.txt` within the `cypress/fixtures` directory. The content written is a stack trace from an Error object.  This test is designed to ensure that Gatsby's security measures prevent arbitrary code execution when processing frontmatter in JavaScript files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/e2e-tests/mdx/src/pages/frontmatter-js.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
(() => {
require(`fs`).writeFileSync(`${process.cwd()}/cypress/fixtures/file-to-attempt-rce-on.txt`, (new Error('Helpful stack trace if this does execute. It should not execute.')).stack)
console.trace()
return {
title: `I should not be parsed`,
otherKey: `Some other key`
}
})()
```

