TITLE: Attempt RCE via JavaScript Frontmatter (Gatsby)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet is designed to be placed within the frontmatter of a Gatsby page. If executed, it would attempt to write a file to the Cypress fixtures directory and log a stack trace, demonstrating a remote code execution (RCE) vulnerability. The test aims to verify that Gatsby prevents execution of JavaScript within frontmatter by default.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/e2e-tests/mdx/src/posts/frontmatter-engine/js-frontmatter.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
(() => {
require(`fs`).writeFileSync(`${process.cwd()}/cypress/fixtures/file-to-attempt-rce-on.txt`, (new Error('Helpful stack trace if this does execute. It should not execute.')).stack)
console.trace()
return {
title: `I should not be parsed`
}
})()
```

